wikipedia_page.main: William Whiteley Lancaster (4 February 1873 – 30 December 1938) was an English first-class cricketer, who played seven games for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1895.Born in Scholes, Huddersfield, Yorkshire, Lancaster was a right-handed batsman, who scored 163 runs at an average of 16.30, with a highest score of 51 against Derbyshire.  A right arm, round arm fast bowler, he bowled five overs for 29 runs without success.Lancaster died in Marsh, Huddersfield, in December 1938, aged 65.
